rmk:
Small voice from resting birds after eating large worms.
Probably referred to as call.  The sound is mostly above 8-9 kHz and
usually lacks fundamentals at 4-5 kHz.
Fundamentals are present at 0:08-0:12 and these sounds
are more easily audible.    The notes lacking fundamentals
are probably difficult to notice and this might explain the lack
of documentation of call of this species.
